I would think that the Warrior would be best to solo Caster mobs, since caster mobs have less HP, a lower melee dmg output and they tend to spent time casting instead of hitting. All the warrior needs then is some good resists gear and a good stun proc / Bash to make sure the caster gets interrupted (an interrupted caster still has its mana so will cast again instead of melee) or resists the spells. <br>
<br>
Of course you have to find the right mobs to kill, you can't go up to just any caster mob and hope to live. After all, the same holds for wizards, they do not snare every mob and start kiting because 1 summon and their 700 AC / 3500 Hp buffed body is getting a serious pounding. (Those PoS frogs wizards kite sometimes put out 1600 dmg in an attack round, wizards that make the mistake of not watching out for those adds die fast.)<br>
