n=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Balancing</span><hr size=1> *Is a necro* who has a warrior alt. <br>
<br>
Classes are becoming very balanced. The gear (buyable) that is available for the average player these days is substantially better then the gear that could be bought 1 year ago. The weapons have improved 200% and wielding a 12/19 can be done for under 4k. With a small raid force (20 toons) you can can get a 44/34. This however is not what makes classes &quot;balanced&quot;. Having 4k More HP and 800 more AC then the average caster is a good start. Plate classes where meant to keep x-mob off Jimmy the wizard, joe the necromancer, boby the ranger, and mike the rogue. <br>
<br>
With out a Plate class, many of these classes would be a fraction as effective. Plate classes are for the most part &quot;the backbone&quot; many groups, and although not substantially increasing DPS themselves, they dramatically increase the DPS of the group, by allowing other classes to go all out DPS.<br>
<br>
If you want the DPS of a rogue or ranger, then what would be the point of these classes? If you want the DPS of a caster, then give my necromancer 4k more HP, and 800 more AC.<br>
<br>
All classes have a purpose, and warriors unfortunately is not DPS, it’s to take the hits so that others may live. This is exactly why I started a warrior, I want to get hit, I like it.<br>
<br>
From a casters perspective, it is nice going all out, and watch 6 dots, do over 1200 damage a tick, and even nicer when you see the 3.2k Crit scroll down with all your DoT damage, but we would never be able to do that with out the warrior.<br>
<br>
In an average group, most casters don’t have the DPS that you are leading on to believe. As a necro in LDON, I get (dps wise) three spells. Horror: 430 damage a tick for 30 seconds. Blood of Thule: 340 damage a tick, and Neuro 1300 damage nuke that crits 15% of the time for UPTO 2600 damage. On single pulls with a chanter or bard I can cast assuming I have PoT9, and bst crack) two Neuros: 2600 damage + pet damage: 600-800ish (depends on pet). That is only 3600-3800 damage to X-mob. With no CC, Necros shine. We can root and rot the add, casting both Horror, and Blood of Thule, while nuking the other target (which is mana intensive), or agro kite add and use Horror, and Blood of Thule all the while Life tapping to compensate for any hits I may take (in a close Quarter fight).<br>
<br>
If you don’t think you do even half that damage, then you may want to go and parse your fight. This also takes mana, when casters are OOM, then how good are we? Melee have sustained DPS, that requires nothing more then haste, and two half decent weapons. <br>
<br>
As far as soloing goes... Yahh its a definite plus, a plus that requires at times multiple deaths. A plus that can be so incredibly boring, at times it is not even worth it. A plus that has been so nerfed, that the average half decent group gets 30 percent more EXP then us. A plus that has so few good spots, that you often find yourself talking in the auction channel, waiting on ricky the wizzie to leave, because they're is simply nothing else to do, and no other camps to go to. I guess its one of those cases that is &quot;be careful what you wish for&quot;. <br>
<br>
I am sure you are also going to play the &quot;you can farm card&quot;. Yahh so what. I need to pay for gear just like you. The big difference is, you don’t have to buy spells. Let me give you a rundown of what my necromancer has spent on spells: Funeral Pyre: 50k, Seduction of saryn: 13K, Touch of death: 10k, Undead mez: 5K, Blood of Thule: 60K, Saryns Companion: 12K, Children of Bertox 30k. 168k for 7 spells.<br>
<br>
But this isn’t what I came to the board for... I have a good idea for snap aggro, and how to make warriors more beneficial, with out throwing out the balance of the game woot woot.<br>
